<h3>Crisis Intervention</h3>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong>For students who are at risk of harming themselves or having a similar significant crisis during office hours (8:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m., Monday - Friday), please contact us at 496-9370 or come directly to our office on the second floor of the Student Health and Counseling Building. Please tell the receptionist that it is an emergency. In an emergency during evening or weekend hours, call 496-HELP (496-4357). There is a therapist on-call 24-hours a day.</p>
<h3>Consultation</h3>
<p>Counselors are available for consultation to bishops, faculty, student groups, wards/stakes, etc. by contacting our office at 496-9370. Students requesting to interview a counselor for a class assignment should email our director, <a href="x24053.xml">Reed Stoddard</a>, and include all pertinent details (purpose of the interview, deadline dates, amount of time needed for the interview, questions, etc.). We prefer to conduct such interviews in student groups and via email when possible.</p>
<h3>Psychiatrist</h3>
<p>Dr. Ronald Zohner is our psychiatrist on staff and he is available by referral through one of our counselors. There is a wait list to meet with Dr. Zohner and a $10.00 fee per appointment.</p>
